Say the three-digit number is abc.
The leftmost digit is double the middle digit --> a=2b;
The number is divisible by 5 --> c is either 0 or 5;
The three digits of a number add up to 17 --> a+b+c=17
So, either a+b+c=2b+b+0=17 or a+b+c=2b+b+5=17. The first equation does not give an integer value of b, so it's not the case. From the second we get that b=4 --> a=8 and c=5 --> a*b*c=160.
